ls cloudsimd/setup/done 2>/dev/null || echo \"Still waiting to the remote machine, please be patient\"'\r\n```\r\nshould work.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Since the starting process is taking a while, one idea is to remove the message:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><span class=\"n\">ls</span><span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">cannot</span> <span class=\"n\">access</span> <span class=\"n\">cloudsim</span><span class=\"sr\">/setup/</span><span class=\"n\">done</span><span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">No</span> <span class=\"n\">such</span> <span class=\"n\">file</span> <span class=\"n\">or</span> <span class=\"n\">directory</span>\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>so the user does not think about a problem in his end and just wait relaxing. Something like:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span>ssh localhost &#39;ls cloudsimd/setup/done 2&gt;/dev/null || echo &quot;Still waiting to the remote machine, please be patient&quot;&#39;\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>should work.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "assignee": null, "state": "new", "version": null, "edited_on": null, "created_on": "2014-02-24T22:48:18.314344+00:00", "milestone": null, "updated_on": "2014-02-24T22:48:18.314344+00:00", "type": "issue", "id": 186}